</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
Conchologically, shells of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. intermedia" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">A. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble those of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. balthica" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="balthica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">A. balthica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latter by higher spire and less inflated body whorl. Modern European authors do not accept 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. intermedia" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">A. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a valid species (
<bibRefCitation author="Gloeer, P" journalOrPublisher="Conchbooks, Hackenheim" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B41" refString="Gloeer, P, 2002. Die Susswassergastropoden Nord- und Mitteleuropas: Bestimmungschlussel, Lebenweise, Verbreitung. Conchbooks, Hackenheim" title="Die Susswassergastropoden Nord- und Mitteleuropas: Bestimmungschlussel, Lebenweise, Verbreitung." year="2002">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Glöer">Gloeer</normalizedToken>
2002
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Welter-Schultes, FW" journalOrPublisher="Planet Poster Editions, Goettingen" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B147" refString="Welter-Schultes, FW, 2012. European Non-Marine Molluscs, a Guide for Species Identification. Planet Poster Editions, Goettingen" title="European Non-Marine Molluscs, a Guide for Species Identification." year="2012">Welter-Schultes 2012</bibRefCitation>
), whereas malacologists of the former USSR still mention this taxon as a species closely allied to 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. balthica" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="balthica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">A. balthica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kruglov, ND" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica: The Russian Malacological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="161 - 180" refId="B70" refString="Kruglov, ND, Starobogatov, YI, 1993b. Annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of the family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda Pulmonata Lymnaeiformes) of Palaearctic and adjacent river drainage areas. Part 2. Ruthenica: The Russian Malacological Journal 3: 161 - 180" title="Annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of the family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda Pulmonata Lymnaeiformes) of Palaearctic and adjacent river drainage areas. Part 2." volume="3" year="1993 b">Kruglov and Starobogatov 1993b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Khokhutkin, IM" journalOrPublisher="Goshchitskiy Publishers, Yekaterinburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="http://herba.msu.ru/shipunov/school/books/khokhutkin2009_limnaeidae.pdf" refId="B58" refString="Khokhutkin, IM, Vinarski, MV, Grebennikov, ME, 2009. Molluscs of the Urals and the Adjacent Areas. The family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Lymnaeiformes). Goshchitskiy Publishers, Yekaterinburg, http://herba.msu.ru/shipunov/school/books/khokhutkin2009_limnaeidae.pdf" title="Molluscs of the Urals and the Adjacent Areas. The family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Lymnaeiformes)." url="http://herba.msu.ru/shipunov/school/books/khokhutkin2009_limnaeidae.pdf" year="2009">Khokhutkin et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Andreeva, SI" journalOrPublisher="The authors, Omsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B7" refString="Andreeva, SI, Andreyev, NI, Vinarski, MV, 2010. Key to freshwater gastropods of Western Siberia (Mollusca: Gastropoda). V. 1. Gastropoda: Pulmonata. Fasc. 1. Families Acroloxidae and Lymnaeidae. The authors, Omsk" title="Key to freshwater gastropods of Western Siberia (Mollusca: Gastropoda). V. 1. Gastropoda: Pulmonata. Fasc. 1. Families Acroloxidae and Lymnaeidae." year="2010">Andreeva et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vinarski, MV" journalOrPublisher="Severtsov Institute of Ecology and Evolution of RAS, Moscow" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B142" refString="Vinarski, MV, Kantor, YI, 2016. Analytical catalogue of fresh and brackish water molluscs of Russia and adjacent countries. A.N. Severtsov Institute of Ecology and Evolution of RAS, Moscow" title="Analytical catalogue of fresh and brackish water molluscs of Russia and adjacent countries. A. N." year="2016">Vinarski and Kantor 2016</bibRefCitation>
). The concept of this species proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kruglov, ND" journalOrPublisher="Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal," pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="1462 - 1473" refId="B64" refString="Kruglov, ND, Starobogatov, YI, 1983b. A contribution to the morphology of European representatives of the subgenus Peregriana of the genus Lymnaea (Gastropoda, Pulmonata). Zoologicheskiy Zhurnal, 62: 1462 - 1473" title="A contribution to the morphology of European representatives of the subgenus Peregriana of the genus Lymnaea (Gastropoda, Pulmonata)." volume="62" year="1983 b">Kruglov and Starobogatov (1983b</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kruglov, ND" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica: The Russian Malacological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="161 - 180" refId="B70" refString="Kruglov, ND, Starobogatov, YI, 1993b. Annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of the family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda Pulmonata Lymnaeiformes) of Palaearctic and adjacent river drainage areas. Part 2. Ruthenica: The Russian Malacological Journal 3: 161 - 180" title="Annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of the family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda Pulmonata Lymnaeiformes) of Palaearctic and adjacent river drainage areas. Part 2." volume="3" year="1993 b">1993b</bibRefCitation>
) coincides with that of old European authors (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.51956" author="Michaud, ALG" journalOrPublisher="Lippman, Verdun" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B87" refString="Michaud, ALG, 1831. Complement de L'histoire Naturelle des Mollusques Terrestres et Fluviatiles de la France, de J.P.R. Draparnaud. Lippman, Verdun, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.51956" title="Complement de L'histoire Naturelle des Mollusques Terrestres et Fluviatiles de la France, de J. P. R. Draparnaud." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.51956" year="1831">Michaud 1831</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.124315" author="Kuester, HC" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica: The Russian Malacological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B71" refString="Kuester, HC, 1862. Die Gattungen Limnaeus, Amphipeplea, Chilina, Isidora und Physopsis. Systematisches Conchylien-Cabinet von Martini und Chemnitz. Bauer und Raspe, Nuernberg 1(17b): 1-48. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.124315" title="Die Gattungen Limnaeus, Amphipeplea, Chilina, Isidora und Physopsis. Systematisches Conchylien-Cabinet von Martini und Chemnitz. Bauer und Raspe, Nuernberg 1 (17 b): 1 - 48." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.124315" year="1862">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Küster">Kuester</normalizedToken>
1862
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Sowerby, GB II" journalOrPublisher="Sowerby, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/8209501" refId="B121" refString="Sowerby, GB II, 1872. Monograph of the genus Limnaea. In: Reeve L. Conchologia Iconica. L. Reeve and Co, London, 18, no pagination, plates 1-15. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/8209501" title="Monograph of the genus Limnaea. In: Reeve L. Conchologia Iconica. L. Reeve and Co, London, 18, no pagination, plates 1 - 15." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/8209501" year="1872">Sowerby 1872</bibRefCitation>
). However, we still do not possess any sequence of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. intermedia" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="intermedia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">A. intermedia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the countries lying east of France and the actual range of this species remains unknown. The Russian authors repeatedly recorded this species from different regions of Russia, including the Urals and Siberia (
<bibRefCitation author="Kruglov, ND" journalOrPublisher="Ruthenica: The Russian Malacological Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="161 - 180" refId="B70" refString="Kruglov, ND, Starobogatov, YI, 1993b. Annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of the family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda Pulmonata Lymnaeiformes) of Palaearctic and adjacent river drainage areas. Part 2. Ruthenica: The Russian Malacological Journal 3: 161 - 180" title="Annotated and illustrated catalogue of species of the family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda Pulmonata Lymnaeiformes) of Palaearctic and adjacent river drainage areas. Part 2." volume="3" year="1993 b">Kruglov and Starobogatov 1993b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Khokhutkin, IM" journalOrPublisher="Goshchitskiy Publishers, Yekaterinburg" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="http://herba.msu.ru/shipunov/school/books/khokhutkin2009_limnaeidae.pdf" refId="B58" refString="Khokhutkin, IM, Vinarski, MV, Grebennikov, ME, 2009. Molluscs of the Urals and the Adjacent Areas. The family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Lymnaeiformes). Goshchitskiy Publishers, Yekaterinburg, http://herba.msu.ru/shipunov/school/books/khokhutkin2009_limnaeidae.pdf" title="Molluscs of the Urals and the Adjacent Areas. The family Lymnaeidae (Gastropoda, Pulmonata, Lymnaeiformes)." url="http://herba.msu.ru/shipunov/school/books/khokhutkin2009_limnaeidae.pdf" year="2009">Khokhutkin et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Andreeva, SI" journalOrPublisher="The authors, Omsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B7" refString="Andreeva, SI, Andreyev, NI, Vinarski, MV, 2010. Key to freshwater gastropods of Western Siberia (Mollusca: Gastropoda). V. 1. Gastropoda: Pulmonata. Fasc. 1. Families Acroloxidae and Lymnaeidae. The authors, Omsk" title="Key to freshwater gastropods of Western Siberia (Mollusca: Gastropoda). V. 1. Gastropoda: Pulmonata. Fasc. 1. Families Acroloxidae and Lymnaeidae." year="2010">Andreeva et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
), but all these records were based solely on morphological data and need to be confirmed molecularly.
</paragraph>
